deck: Sexy comic adventures of a boy under military service in the Italy of the 70's
description:
Il Tromba was published at first by Geis, which later became the most famous Edifumetto.

Starting in June 1975, the series includes 144 regular numbers and 8 supplements (#40,58,67,70,106,118,125,131 suppl.), and is about the sexy comic adventures of a boy (Adriano Lentano a.k.a. "Il Tromba") under military service in the Italy of the 70's.

Other previously unreleased stories of 16 tables can be found on the magazine "Odeon", in the years 1977/1978.
name: Il Tromba
